name: 李老师不是你老师
content: When I went to bed last night, I suddenly remembered a post I saw on Weibo a few years ago. The blogger was a chemist. When the anti-PX demonstration took place in Xiamen, he thought that the common people were too stupid and had no scientific knowledge at all. It was not until the PX factory that moved to Zhangzhou exploded twice that he realized that the common people might not understand chemistry, but they certainly understand China. In fact, this sentence is still applicable today.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
For ordinary people, many second-, third- and fourth-tier small cities have been closed less than two or three times in the three years of the epidemic, and they don’t want their "normal" lives to be disturbed.
As for whether the virus is deadly, is it important? This is the least important thing.
After thinking about it, just like Xiamen citizens don’t trust chemical plants, everyone says thank you for the country’s three years of protection, but they know in their hearts that once they let go of this, the government will definitely not be able to manage it well.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
As soon as the State Council's 20-point policy was released, the Internet was full of vigorous strangling of "lying bandits", which fully proved that once the government was said to be relaxed, everyone directly assumed that the government would lie down. They did not believe what the 20-point policy said at all, which shows that everyone actually understands China.
Unconditional support for the government is just a slogan to protect oneself.
Two days of relaxation proved that this is indeed the case.
To put it bluntly, you have locked down the city in a mess, and everyone dare not believe that you have the ability to relax.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
So I found that the discussion may have started in the wrong direction. People don't care about science at all. They are all relying on survival instincts.
Everyone knows that good things don't come to you, but you will be the one who suffers in the end. So instead of letting go and being tossed, it's better to watch the snowflakes fall.
It wasn't until the heavy snow flooded the roof and collapsed the house that I had to shout tremblingly
